# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Step-by-step Deobfuscation

The code uses several obfuscation techniques:
1. **String array with Base64 encoding** - `a0_0x1c75()` returns an array of Base64-encoded strings
2. **Lookup function** - `a0_0x42e7()` decodes and retrieves strings by index
3. **Control flow flattening** - `switch/case` with string-ordered execution (e.g., `"8|6|7|9|2|1|5|3|4|0".split("|")`)
4. **Proxy objects** - Objects wrapping simple arithmetic operations

## Deobfuscated Code

```javascript
// Constants
const TAU = 6.283;          // 2π
const PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
const SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // √(1/2)

// Physics/simulation configuration
const config = {
    repulsion: 4000,
    compliance: 0.004,
    refractory: 0.92,       // Velocity damping factor
    diffusion: 0.0003,      // Centering force
    saturation: 40,          // Max particle count
    resistance: 0.04,        // Particle drag
    diastolic: 0.06          // Camera smoothing factor
};

// === NODES (graph vertices) ===
const nodes = [
    { id: "hub",     label: "Hub",     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// === EDGES (spring connections) ===
const edges = [
    { a: "hub",   b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// === CAMERA ===
let camera       = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
let cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// === PARTICLES ===
let particles = [];
let frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// === PHYSICS STEP ===
function physicsStep() {
    // 1) Node-node REPULSION (Coulomb-like)
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            const dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            const dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            const force = config.repulsion / (dist * dist);
            const fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            const fy = (dy / dist) * force;

            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2) Edge SPRING forces (Hooke's law)
    for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        const nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
        const nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        const dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        const dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        const displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
        const force = (edges[i].k || config.compliance) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3) CENTERING force + velocity damping + position integration
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.diffusion;   // Pull toward center (400, 300)
        nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.diffusion;
        nodes[i].vx *= config.refractory;   // Damping (0.92)
        nodes[i].vy *= config.refractory;
        nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;          // Euler integration
        nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
    }
}

// === SPAWN PARTICLES ===
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.saturation) return;  // Max 40 particles

    const sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    const angle = Math.random() * TAU;           // Random direction
    const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;  // 0.3 to ~1.0

    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,     // Lifetime: 800–2000 frames
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF  // 0.8 to ~1.94
    });
}

// === UPDATE PARTICLES ===
function updateParticles() {
    for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        const p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.resistance * 0.125;  // Slight drag (0.995)
        p.vy *= 1 - config.resistance * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);  // Remove dead particles
    }
}

// === UPDATE CAMERA (smooth follow) ===
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x    += (cameraTarget.x    - camera.x)    * config.diastolic;
    camera.y    += (cameraTarget.y    - camera.y)    * config.diastolic;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom)  * config.diastolic;
}

// === MAIN LOOP ===
function tick() {
    physicsStep();
    updateParticles();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();  // Spawn every 3rd frame
    updateCamera();
    frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16);  // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** with ambient particles — essentially the **physics engine** for an interactive node-graph visualization:

| System | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Graph Layout** | 6 nodes connected by 8 edges, arranged using a force-directed algorithm |
| **Repulsion** | All nodes repel each other (inverse-square law, like electrical charges) |
| **Springs** | Connected nodes are pulled together by spring forces (Hooke's law) with configurable rest lengths |
| **Centering** | A weak gravity pulls all nodes toward (400, 300) |
| **Damping** | Velocities are multiplied by 0.92 each frame to prevent oscillation |
| **Particles** | Decorative particles spawn from random nodes, drift outward, and fade/die after 800–2000 frames |
| **Camera** | Smoothly interpolates toward a target position/zoom (easing factor 0.06) |
| **Main loop** | Runs at ~60 FPS via `setInterval(..., 16)` |

The code contains **no rendering** — this is purely the simulation state. A separate (missing) rendering module would read the `nodes`, `edges`, `particles`, and `camera` state to draw them on a canvas. The visual result would be something like an **animated network diagram with floating particles** — commonly seen in portfolio sites, dashboards, or "tech-looking" backgrounds.
